{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Shiferaw et al. [96] also reported a 29% increase in compressive strength at a 15% ESP replacement level, confirming its potential to enhance concrete's structural integrity.",
    "Studies have shown that using glass powder as a supplementary material in concrete can significantly improve its mechanical properties.",
    "Ibrahim and Meawad [97] found that soda lime glass powder increased compressive strength by 10-20% and improved flexural strength at replacement levels of 10%, 15%, and 20% due to its fine particle size and reactivity.",
    "Patel et al. [98] also reported that fine glass powders (GP63 and GP75) enhanced compressive and flexural strength, particularly at a 10-15% replacement level.",
    "Baikerikar et al. [99] observed that WGP and sand increased compressive strength by 12-18% and split tensile strength by 8% at a 10% replacement level."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
